The TDD exercise is complete. All 9 tests for Conway's Game of Life are implemented and passing:

1. Empty grid returns empty grid
2. Single live cell dies (underpopulation)
3. Two live cells die (underpopulation)
4. Live cell with 2 neighbors survives
5. Live cell with 3 neighbors survives
6. Live cell with 4+ neighbors dies (overpopulation)
7. Dead cell with exactly 3 neighbors becomes alive (reproduction)
8. 2x2 block remains unchanged (still life)
9. Blinker transforms from vertical to horizontal (oscillator)

The implementation in `src/game-of-life.ts` uses a bounded `boolean[][]` representation with a `countNeighbors` helper and `survives`/`isReborn` variables that cleanly express the two Game of Life transition rules.
